The Swiss National Bank took in an estimated US$39 billion worth of assets in 2008, as a part of a government bailout, integrating them in the so called stabilization fund. Under the terms of the deal between UBS and the Swiss National Bank, UBS can repurchase the fund once the Swiss National Bank loan investment on the fund was paid in full.
